name: Forest
description:
I make these bracelets one by one as they're ordered, so please give me one week to make and get it in the mail to you. When you pay for this bracelet, be sure to let me know your wrist size so that it's a perfect fit. Note: colors may differ slightly.

I find the rocks for these bracelets along the banks of the Methow River. I drill the rock to create a simple button. The (peridot) green and black beads are carefully braided on charcoal-colored waxed linen so that the bracelet is durable and attractive. Adorned with small sterling silver beads. Secures with a beaded loop clasp.

Stack this bracelet with others for a gorgeous Bohemian look.

River rocks symbolize strength, age, wisdom, and earth.

Custom order this bracelet so that it fits your wrist perfectly.

name: Firethorn
description:
I love wearing yellow at this time of year to add a little cheer to darker days. Here is a simple, rustic necklace with wire wrapped yellow marble - marble beads made from recycled counter tops. It's inspired by bold yellow Firethorn berries.

This artisan made mixed media necklace also includes sterling silver and natural river rocks. I collected and drilled the tiny rocks and hand formed the sterling silver links and hook clasp.

This necklace measures 22 inches, and is designed to be adjustable (smaller).

name: Orbit
description:
With this artisan necklace, sterling silver carves a celestial path around a moon, a tiny natural river rock.

The free-flowing pendant hangs from an 18 inch sterling silver diamond cut ball chain. The pendant hangs 6cm x 4cm.

Sweet and simple.

name: Waterfall
description:
Reminiscent of a waterfall: handmade sterling silver chains, light blue semi-precious gemstones, and a natural river rock.

This artisan made, triple stacking bracelet measures 18cm. I individually hand formed and soldered each link. It closes with a hand made toggle and clasp.

name: Glow
description:
Sunset sifts through clouds
as evening whispers darkness--
last warm summer glow.

- Jonathan Caswell

Size 6.5, this ring is made with sterling silver, natural river rock and a glowing yellow felt. Dimensions of the rock are 1.75cm x 1.5cm.

name: Firethorn Earrings
description:
Here is a pair of a simple, rustic earrings with wire wrapped yellow marble - marble beads made from recycled counter tops. They are inspired by bold yellow Firethorn berries.

These artisan made mixed media earrings also includes sterling silver and natural river rocks. I collected and drilled the tiny rocks and hand formed the sterling silver.

Match these earrings with my Firethorn necklace to create a beautiful set:
http://www.nicoleringgold.com/product/firethorn

name: Columbia
description:
I found this little rock along the Columbia River at Walla Walla State Park in Wenatchee. It is simple and beautiful - black with natural gray and white swirls.

This artisan ring is made with sterling silver, size 7.

name: Skipping Rocks
description:
This necklace is inspired by the simple pleasure of skipping rocks. I collected and drilled the tiny rocks, hand made the chain and hook clasp.

This necklace measures 22.5 inches at its longest, and is designed to be adjustable.

name: Simple
description:
This simple, minimalist pendant necklace is made with sterling silver and natural river rock. I first drilled the river rock, and then shaped the silver so that it weaves through the rock and around the chain.

The silver ball chain measures 16 inches. The rock pendant hangs 2" in length.

name: Homme de la Montagne
description:
I picture this particular leather band on a man, but it definitely could be worn by a woman as well. It is 8 inches round, and 1.5 inches wide.

This simple, minimalist artisan-made bracelet combines leather, sterling silver, and natural rock.

name: Exuberant
description:
ex·u·ber·ant

adjective: exuberant

1.
filled with or characterized by a lively energy and excitement.

These hoop-style artisan earrings are made with sterling silver, natural river rocks, and a combination of gemstones: carnelian, aquamarine, citrine, and garnet. They measure 6cm in length.

name: Atlas
description: These artisan made earrings hang 5.5cm. They are 2cm wide at the base. I made them with sterling silver and natural river rock.

name: Ruins
description:
Inspired by the ruins we saw throughout Turkey, this is a rustic and elegant ring. It's made with sterling silver and brass - cut, shaped, hammered, soldered, and polished. I made it with leftover metal scraps, so it's absolutely one of a kind.

This ring is size 6. The band width is 1.6cm.

name: Three Moons
description:
Three natural rocks from the Methow River, carefully drilled. The rocks are beige, gray, and a light speckled gray.

The cord is made with waxed linen, and secures with a drilled river rock button.

The cord for this necklace measures 38cm.

name: Golden Tears
description:
Life in the fast lane is lonely at the top.
Golden Tears, 1979

These hoop-style artisan earrings are made with sterling silver, natural river rocks, and citrine gemstones. They measure 4.25cm in length.

name: THrē
description: This is a set of three simple sterling silver bangles, hand hammered. Each bangle contains a small, natural river rock found near my home in the Methow Valley. The diameter of each bangle is 7cm.

name: Stalactite
description:
Inspired by an ice formation that I saw hovering above a stream the other day, this necklace is made with sterling silver and natural river rocks.

A stalactite formation comes from the Greek word "stalasso", which means "to drip". A stalactite is a type of formation that hangs from ceilings, and contains material that is soluble, can be deposited, is in suspension, or is capable of being melted.

This necklace is adjustable between 17.5-19 inches. The geometric-style, free-moving pendant hangs an additional  3 inches. I placed a small drilled river rock at the end of the silver chain.

This is a very unique piece, one-of-a-kind.

name: Snowball Fight
description:
Honestly? I've never been a big fan of having hard snowballs hit my head, break apart and tumble down my neck. Where exactly is the fun in that?

However, I do like watching snowball fights, from carefully packing the snow to launching the attack. It makes me laugh, and I'm grateful not to be struck.

These fun Snowball Fight earrings hang 7cm. They're made with sterling silver, quartz, and natural river rock.

name: Silver Clouds
description:
The shy Moon peeps
thru the veil of clouds
a game of hide n seek

Articulated forged sterling silver circles are riveted together to form a line of clouds. A natural rock is nestled in the center, symbolizing a moon. The cloud shaped silver has a beaten texture to bring forth the rough hewn surface. The chain is 20cm long. The widest point of the bracelet is 2cm.

name: Interpret
description:
in·ter·pret
verb \in-ˈtər-prət, -pət\

: to explain the meaning of (something)

: to understand (something) in a specified way

: to perform (something, such as a song or a role) in a way that shows your own thoughts and feelings about it

This artisan necklace is made with sterling silver and three natural river rocks. The silver chain is entirely handmade, and it secures with a hook clasp. The necklace measures 20.5 inches.

name: Swing
description:
autumn twilight
my parents in silence
on the swing
- Ramesh Anand

These artisan made earrings hand 5.5cm. They are 2cm wide at the base. I made them with sterling silver, clear glass beads and natural river rock.

name: Cairn (small)
description:
These smaller cairn necklaces are small enough for those who prefer smaller pendants. No one piece is the same, but generally measure 2.5" wide.

I make these smaller cairns when you place your order, so they're custom made.

I hand select the rocks along the banks of the river by my home. I then hollow out and drill the rocks. This pendants are strung with dark brown waxed linen cord. They tie in the back with a simple knot.

River rocks symbolize strength, age, wisdom, and earth.

name: Sage
description:
This artisan-made piece can be worn as a long necklace or as a leather wrap bracelet (it wraps around my wrist 4 times). Mixed media including leather, natural river rocks, African trade beads, and handmade sterling silver links and clasp.

I love throwing a few of these artsy strands around my neck at one time for an ethnic look.

This sage colored piece measures 27 inches. It closes with a handmade sterling silver hook clasp.

name: Saagi
description:
In Africa, I lived in a village called Ouna, nestled along the banks of the Niger River. Almost every day I took a walk in the brush ("saagi") along the river with my deaf friend Mamoudou. Together, we collected greens ("kopto") for dinner, and dipped our feet in the river.

The neutral colors of these natural rocks remind me of Ouna.

This is a bulky ring that's somewhat adjustable between sizes 7 and 8.5. Two natural rocks fit snugly on both sides of your finger - made with sterling silver. The larger rock measures 2 x 2cm, and the smaller measures 1 x 1cm.

name: Secret Love Notes
description:
“See how she leans her cheek upon her hand.
O, that I were a glove upon that hand
That I might touch that cheek!”
― William Shakespeare, Romeo and Juliet 

These one-of-a-kind artisan earrings are made with oxidized sterling silver, 14K gold and natural river rocks. They hang 5.5cm.

name: Fledgling
description:
This piece can be worn as a necklace or as a bulky leather wrap bracelet (it wraps around my wrist 3 times). Mixed media, including leather, oxidized sterling silver chain, natural river rocks, royal blue African trade beads, a silver owl bead, and handmade sterling silver links.

This artisan made piece measures 19.5 inches.

name: Le Môle
description:
Le Môle (1,864m) is an intriguing isolated peak with beautiful views over the Mont Blanc range, on the outskirts of Samoens, France. The name “Samoëns” dates from 1167 A.D. and is based on a medieval expression meaning “the seven mountains”, a reference to the peaks around the village.

My parents spend several months each year in Samoens. Their small chalet is situated on the Giffre. Fortunately for me, they spent countless hours collecting rocks to bring home for me to incorporate into my jewelry.

This ring is made with sterling silver and a naturally striped stone from the Giffre. Size 6. The band width is .05cm. The stone measures 1.75x1cm.

One of a kind.

description:

This is a simple, minimalist pendant necklace that is made with sterling silver and natural river rock. I first drilled the river rock, and then shaped the silver so that it weaves through the rock. Each link is hand formed and soldered, and the silver has been oxidized.

The necklace measures 17.25 inches. The rock pendant hangs 5cm in length.

name: Al Mio Amore
description:
Al mio amore - To my darling.

What else can I say? This natural plum-red river rock, sterling silver and gold ring speaks for itself.

Size -9. One of a kind.

description:

name: A + B + C = 180°
description:
This simple pendant necklace is made with sterling silver and natural river rock. I first drilled the river rock, and then shaped the silver so that it weaves through the rock and around the leather cord. This pendant holds an interesting balance between natural, organic and straight, geometric lines.

The leather cord measures 22.5 inches. It closes with a hand shaped (geometric-style) hook clasp. The rock pendant hangs 2.5" in length.

name: Interweave
description:
This unique, bulky ring is entwined with contemporary notions of beauty, love, and acceptance - sterling silver and and natural river rock.

Size 6, but I can make a similar one for you in a different size, per your request. Note that no two rings will be exactly the same, and river rocks will vary in appearance. The bottom of ring measures .05cm, and the top measures 2.25cm.

name: Honesty
description:
Thank you to my unbelievable community for brainstorming words to turn into unique, one-of-a-kind charms. My friend Jen suggested the word "honesty".

This piece can be worn as a long necklace or as a leather wrap bracelet (it wraps around my wrist 4 times). Mixed media, including leather, natural river rocks, African trade beads, and handmade sterling silver charms and links.

This artisan made piece measures 27 inches. It closes with a handmade sterling silver hook clasp.

name: Chardonnay
description:
I love making these jewelry links! It's my new obsession.

Rustic, simple, light, delicate (although not fragile).

These earrings are entirely hand made with oxidized sterling silver and Citrone gemstones. They hang 4.5cm.

name: Log Fence
description:
The sterling silver wire, jump rings and joints were all formed and soldered together by me to make this unique artisan bracelet. The design reminds me of a log fence. It moves wonderfully - doesn't kink. The silver is oxidized to give it a rustic look. The clasp is a simple hook with a natural river rock dangling at one end.

This bracelet would work on someone with wrists 7.5 inches or smaller. My wrists measure 7", and the bracelet hangs a little loose.  It's super comfortable to wear.

name: Fire Spinner Cairn
description:
Cairn is a man-made stack of stones. It comes from the Scottish Gaelic: càrn. Cairns are found all over the world in uplands, on moorland and mountaintops, near waterways, on sea cliffs, and in barren desert and tundra areas.

Today, cairns are generally erected as landmarks. Throughout history, they have also been built as tombs, or used for defensive, hunting, ceremonial, and other purposes.

This cairn pendant is 4cm wide and 2.75cm (height), and secures with a simple drilled river rock button clasp.

I hand select the rocks along the banks of the river by my home. I then hollow out and drill the rocks. The orange and purple spiral Lampwork glass bead is hand made by J. Veda Jones.

This pendant is strung with dark brown waxed linen cord.

River rocks symbolize strength, age, wisdom, and earth.

name: Chain Links
description:
Everything in this necklace is handmade, sterling silver and one hollowed river rock that works like a link. It moves wonderfully - doesn't kink. The silver is oxidized to give it a rustic look. The clasp is a simple hook.

The necklace measures 19 inches. It's designed so that no one point is the front or back. Every part of it is interesting, and it's lovely when worn with a fancy gown or a cowgirl hat, shit-kickers and jeans.

name: Fleur
description:
Magnolia petals
Folded over like wet boots
Line the garden path

- Anonymous

Simple flowers hand made with sterling silver, then oxidized for a rustic, earthy appearance. These artisan earrings measure 7cm.

name: Abundance
description:
Thank you to my unbelievable community for brainstorming words to turn into unique, one-of-a-kind pieces. My friend Danica suggested the word "abundance".

This is an unusual pendant. I hand formed a rectangular sterling silver box and filled it with small river rocks. I then grouted the rocks in place.

The pendant measures 8cm x 2cm. The leather cord measures 19 inches. It secures with a simple handmade sterling silver hook clasp.

name: Discovery
description:
eating mushrooms is
eating earth made food—everything
but the grit

- David Marshall

Sterling silver earrings, lightly twisting, with small Labradorite and Carnelian gemstones dangling from each end. These earrings hang 5.5cm.

name: Mère et de L'enfant
description:
Mother and Child natural river rocks ring.

This is a bulky ring that's somewhat adjustable between sizes 5.5 and 6.5. Two natural rocks fit snugly on both sides of your finger - made with sterling silver. The larger rock measures 2 x 2cm, and the smaller measures .5 x 1.5cm.

name: Le Grand Massif
description:
My parents found this natural striped rock from the Giffre, a river that runs by their chalet in Samoens, France. During the winter months, they ski in the mountains that tower above the Giffre, thoroughly enjoying the enormous terrain of the Grand Massif. Hence, the name for this unique ring.

Size 8, this ring is made with sterling silver, natural sedimentary  river rock and green felt. Dimensions of the rock are 2cm x 3cm.

name: Alpine Lake
description:
Imagine a long day's hike. The sky is bright blue, the vegetation lush and green. There is a gentle breeze causing leaves to flutter, creating a soft tapping rhythm. When you reach your destination, an alpine lake nestled beneath jagged peaks, the water is so clear you can see the rocks at the bottom. Without hesitation, you jump in.

This necklace takes me to that place. Made with turquoise, peridot, a combination of semi-precious gems, sterling silver, and natural rock. It measures 53cm round.

name: Joy
description:
Thank you to my unbelievable community for brainstorming words to turn into unique, one-of-a-kind charms. My friend Meg suggested the word "joy".

This beaded aqua gemstone leather bracelet is flexible and light to wear. The sterling silver charm is hand-hammered, soldered, and securely strung onto the leather. This bracelet can be stacked with others to create a Bohemian look, or it can be worn solo.

These bracelets have 2 snaps so are adjustable in size, either 17cm or 19cm.

name: Breathe
description:
Thank you to my wonderful community for brainstorming words to turn into unique, one-of-a-kind charms. My dear childhood friend Josephine suggested the word "breathe".

This necklace is comfortable and very light to wear. The sterling silver charm is hand-hammered and soldered, combined with a simple stone that my parents found in Samoens, France.

Made with brown leather and sterling silver. A small drilled river rock dangles at the end. The cord measures 60cm, and is adjustable to 66cm.

name: Soleil Rouge
description:
When I made this ring, I envisioned a red sun sitting on the horizon. In Niger, we often camped on the side of an old airport strip that overlooked the border of Benin, just across the Niger River. We'd chat over camp fires, watching the sun turn red, big and round, just before disappearing for the night.

Size 7, this ring is made with sterling silver, natural river rock and red felt. Dimensions of the rock are 2.5cm x 1.75cm.

name: Gealach
description:
The rock for this ring was found on Deception Pass. It sparkles slightly, almost like it was sprinkled with pixie dust. It reminds me of a shimmering full moon.

This ring is size 8. The rock is 1.25cm in diameter. Made with sterling silver and a natural rock.

name: Sea Breeze
description:
This glass turquoise beaded leather bracelet is flexible and lightweight. The sterling silver strip is hand-hammered and securely strung onto the leather. The beads come from Ghana. This bracelet can be stacked with others to create a Bohemian look, or it can be worn solo.

These bracelets have 2 snaps so are adjustable in size, either 17cm or 19cm.

name: Stones
description:
In the Utter silence of a temple,
A cicada’s voice alone
Penetrates the rocks

— Matsuo Basho

Simple, natural stone earrings and oxidized sterling silver. 4.5cm in length.

name: Health
description:
What comes to mind when you're hiking, biking, running, swimming, harvesting your garden, walking the beach, doing yoga, or breathing fresh air? For me - health. 

Each piece in this bracelet has been handmade, including the clasps, charms, and drilled rock. Mixed media including sterling silver, leather, and rocks.

This health bracelet measures 18cm. Send me a message if you would like a similar bracelet made in a different size or with a different blessing.

The (13mm) chain measures 18 inches.

River rocks symbolize strength, age, wisdom, and earth.

description:
This sunflower pendant is made with sterling silver, cut, formed, melted and soldered into one full piece. The focal point is amber-colored glass. I oxidized the silver to give it a rustic appearance.

The pendant measures 3cm in diameter. It is strung on a brown leather cord, and secures with a hand formed sterling silver clasp, embellished with a dangling silver owl drop. The cord measures 49cm.

description:

name: Sprout
description:
I make these bracelets one by one as they're ordered, so please give me one week to make and get it in the mail to you. When you pay for this bracelet, be sure to let me know your wrist size so that it's a perfect fit. Note: colors may differ slightly.

I find the rocks for these bracelets along the banks of the Methow River. I drill the rock to create a simple button. The (real) turquoise and green beads are carefully braided on chocolate brown waxed linen so that the bracelet is durable and attractive. Adorned with small sterling silver beads and a small leaf charm. Secures with a beaded loop clasp.

Stack this bracelet with others for a gorgeous Bohemian look.

River rocks symbolize strength, age, wisdom, and earth.

This bracelet measures 19cm round. I can make it in a different size, per your request.

name: Pétales
description:
For this bracelet, I used sterling silver wire for the petals, melted wire into balls and soldered them to the petals. I hammered the balls flat and drilled holes through them for jump rings. Et voilà!

This artisan-made bracelet is adjustable (20-25cm). At the end hangs a natural river rock collected from the banks of the Methow River.

name: Tag, You're It
description: I love these simple dangling earrings. They are lightweight and swing easily. They're made with sterling silver and natural river rocks. I made each link and soldered the loops, so they're very secure. They hang 6.5cm.

name: Sun Rays
description:
Sun Rays, made with sterling silver, cut, formed, melted and soldered into one full piece. The center point is a natural rock, smoothed to perfection by our local river.

The pendant measures 5x5cm. It is strung on a brown leather cord, and secures with a hand drilled river rock button. The cord measures 41cm.

name: Synergy
description:
This is a simple toggle and clasp necklace, hand made with sterling silver, natural river rocks and leather.

The necklace measures 16 inches, but can be adjustable (shorter, not longer) as the toggle is designed to slip in and out of the clasp, then rest comfortably below your neck.

name: Citron
description:
During these darker fall days, as we head into winter, Citrine has become my new favorite gemstone. I love working with the cheerful, heart-warming yellow.

These earrings are made with sterling silver, natural river rock, and Citrine. They measure 5cm (and 1.75cm wide).

name: Wheels of Life
description:
Sometimes I imagine myself spinning on a wheel. I consider each area of my life and assess what feels off balance, and then make subtle (or even dramatic) shifts to regain equilibrium.

These simple mixed metal earrings bring that imagery into play. 14K gold "beads" spin freely on sterling silver hoops. Handmade gold ear wires. These artisan-made earrings hang 4cm in length.

name: Wonder
description:
Playful sterling silver metal twirls around smooth red leather cord. I made each little twisted charm, with balls on either side so that it can spin around the leather freely as it's worn. Closes with a silver button clasp.

The leather cord measures 37cm round.

name: Susan
description:
This necklace is named Susan because I happened to be talking with my dear friend Susan while it was in process.

Did you know that the name Susan derives from Middle Egyptian "sšn" meaning lotus flower?

A combination of sterling silver, natural rock and leather, this artisan-made necklace is adjustable between 20-22 inches. It hooks with a handmade clasp. Each bead is heated and hand formed. It's one of a kind.

name: A Confluence of Rivers
description:
Where stream meets river, currents wrap around perfectly polished stones.

This necklace is artisan-made with sterling silver and natural river rocks. It measures 22.5 inches. The pendant is made with 2 individual swirling pieces, symbolic of a confluence of rivers.

name: Echo
description:
Each piece in this bracelet has been handmade, including the links, clasp, charms, and drilled rocks. Mixed media including sterling silver, leather, and rocks.

This health bracelet measures 14.75 inches, designed to wrap twice around your wrist.

name: Ihinka
description:
"Ihinka" means "Two" in Zarma, the language I spoke while I lived in Niger.

Two Haiku:

that daft dog
chasing the train
then letting it go

dumb bumblebee
bumps the windowpane
again again again

-Alan Spence

Two natural river rocks performing a balancing act on either end of a spiraling sterling silver ring. Adjustable.

name: Grace
description:
Circular, hoop-ish earrings made with sterling silver and natural river rocks from the Methow River.

The earrings hang 6cm. I used sterling silver wire to make the circles, and drilled holes through the tiny rocks. Simple, eco-friendly, fun.

name: Embrace
description:
I love this ring! It's playful, natural, down to earth, sophisticated, and comfortable.

This is a simple and elegant ring. It's made with sterling silver. A natural river rock is framed in the middle.

This ring is size 7. The band width is 1.5cm.

name: Trapeze
description:
Have you ever watched a flying trapeze artist, as she grabs the trapeze bar and jumps off the towering platform? My heart always skips several beats when the performer releases the bar, trusting that the next performer will grab hold of her wrists while hanging by his knees on another trapeze. The timing must be perfect.

This trapeze necklace is made with sterling silver and natural river rocks. I drilled the rocks and shaped/soldered the silver links. The triple pendant hangs from a sterling silver neck cable, 18 inches round. The pendant hangs 3.5 inches in length.

name: Cairn
description:
Cairn is a man-made stack of stones. It comes from the Scottish Gaelic: càrn. Cairns are found all over the world in uplands, on moorland and mountaintops, near waterways, on sea cliffs, and in barren desert and tundra areas.

Today, cairns are generally erected as landmarks. Throughout history, they have also been built as tombs, or used for defensive, hunting, ceremonial, and other purposes.

This cairn pendant is 4cm wide and 3.8cm (height), and secures with a simple drilled river rock button clasp.

I hand select the rocks along the banks of the river by my home. I then hollow out and drill the rocks. This pendant is strung with dark brown waxed linen cord.

River rocks symbolize strength, age, wisdom, and earth.

name: Cranberry Drops
description: Little cranberry colored pearls dangle from natural river rocks (that I collected from the Methow River near our home). Oxidized sterling silver wire, hand-formed, artisan made. These sweet earrings hang 5.5cm.

name: Figure Skate
description:
When I was young my mom would take us ice skating. While I skated in circles, struggling to keep my ankles from caving in, my mother would dance from one foot to the other, carving figure eights into the ice.

These earrings are made with sterling silver. They are 3cm wide and hang 6.5cm.

name: Ripples
description:
passing summer wind
sweetly kisses pond’s surface
stirring memories
- Merlin Spielen

Inspired by ripples, this necklace is made with sterling silver and natural river rocks from the Methow River. The artisan made pendant measures 3.5cm in diameter. The silver neck wire measures 18cm.

name: Grow
description:
This is definitely a more rustic artisan piece, with well-worked recycled sterling silver. I hammered, heated and manipulated it a bunch to maneuver the pieces into place.

The focal point is a natural quartz river rock, secured to the center with 14K gold. Also inside the center are small leaves that spell out the word "Grow".

This pendant measures 1.5" in diameter. It hangs from an 18" sterling silver neck wire.

name: Three Cairns
description:
I selected the rocks for along the banks river near my home. I then hollowed out and drilled the rock. This necklace is strung with dark brown waxed linen cord, and secures with a drilled river rock button.

River rocks symbolize strength, age, wisdom, and earth.

This necklace measures 18cm from button to pendant, and 9mm across the pendant.

name: Giffre
description:
The Giffre River runs through Samoens, France. The name “Samoëns” dates from 1167 A.D. and is based on a mediaeval expression meaning “the seven mountains”, a reference to the peaks around the village

My parents spend several months each year in Samoens. Their small chalet is situated on the Giffre. Fortunately for me, they spent countless hours collecting rocks to bring home for me to incorporate into my jewelry.

This ring is made with sterling silver and a naturally striped, perfectly polished stone from the Giffre. Size 7. The band width is 1.5cm. The stone measures 2x1.5cm.

One of a kind.

name: Twilight
description:
I make these bracelets one by one as they're ordered, so please give me one week to make and get it in the mail to you. When you pay for this bracelet, be sure to let me know your wrist size so that it's a perfect fit. Note: colors may differ slightly.

I find the rocks for these bracelets along the banks of the Methow River. I drill the rock to create a simple button. The gray and black seed beads are carefully braided on charcoal waxed linen so that the bracelet is durable and attractive. Adorned with sterling silver and gemstone beads. Secures with a beaded loop clasp.

Stack this bracelet with others for a gorgeous Bohemian look.

River rocks symbolize strength, age, wisdom, and earth.

name: Entwined
description:
Hands entwined. Fingers laced.

This unique, bulky ring is entwined with contemporary notions of beauty, love, and acceptance - sterling silver flirting with 14K gold.

Size 7.5, but I can make a similar one for you in a different size, per your request. The bottom of ring measures 1cm, and the top measures 2.5cm.

name: Tranquility
description:
My tranquility?
I found it
Amidst the chaos....

- Zoe Jones

Three natural river rocks framed with sterling silver - the colors of each rock purposely unmatched. These earrings hang almost 4cm, and are 2cm wide.

name: Daisy
description:
This flower pendant is made with sterling silver and natural rock. I cut, formed and soldered the silver into one full piece. The center point is a rock, smoothed to perfection by our local river.

The pendant measures 5x2cm. It is strung on a brown leather cord, and secures with a hand drilled river rock button. The cord measures 41cm.

name: Plankton
description:
This focal point of this sterling silver necklace is a natural rock, smoothed to perfection by our local river. The nine plankton-inspired pendants work together, swinging freely on the oxidized sterling silver chain.

The rock pendant measures 7cm (length). Together, all nine pendants measure 6cm (width). The chain is 18in around.

This necklace is one of a kind.

name: Grasshopper
description:
Grasshopper Pass is a section of the Pacific Crest trail starting just south of Harts Pass in Washington's North Cascades. The hike offers panoramic views of mountains and forests as you hike along the upper ridges of the mountains - simply stunning.

This ring is made with sterling silver and a natural green rock that I found as I was hiking over Grasshopper Pass. Size 7. The spriraling band width is 1.5cm. The stone measures 1.5 x 2cm.

name: Straw Bales
description:
Inspired by straw bales, these simple, rustic and elegant earrings are made with sterling silver and brass. I cut, shaped, hammered, soldered, and polished them with leftover scraps.

The earrings hang 7cm, and they're almost 2cm wide at the base.

name: Winter Moons
description:
In the night of the winter moon
Small stones
Touch the bottom of my shoes

— Yosano Buson

Simple, natural stone earrings and oxidized sterling silver. 4.5cm in length.
